From 7339f82a5818c096e01ffe9575b7d7ba4f668897 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dev <dev@local>
Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 09:49:16 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: traction crossover-upshift relearn hotkey + learning
 status indicator
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Add an F7 (editable) hotkey that relearns the current car's crossover-upshift
model — wipes its gear ratios + power curve in memory and in the persisted
profile and rebuilds from telemetry, keeping the rev-limiter envelope, mirroring
T-GT II reset-current. Surface a learning-status indicator in the HUD chrome bar
(all 3 templates) and the gear-calibration card on the web dashboard and Electron
overview: LEARNING (yellow) until gear ratios + power curve are both learned,
LEARNED (green), and RELEARNING (blue) for 5s after the hotkey. Status flows
through the telemetry snapshot so HUD and dashboard stay consistent. EN + zh-CN.

Bump 13.3.0.
